.DT
playerkillers
$MUDNAME$ player help
playerkillers

.SH Name
.SP 5 5
playerkillers - List the player killers currently logged in.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SP 5 5
playerkillers [brief|verbose]
.EP
.SP 5 5
playerk [brief|verbose]
.EP
.SP 5 5
pks [brief|verbose]
.EP
.SP 5 5
pk [brief|verbose]
.EP

.SH Description
.SP 5 5
Playerkillers lists the player killers who are currently logged on.  In verbose
mode players' family names are also listed with families grouped together;
the default is brief which gives just the first name.

You can also use this command to show all the current player killers in
the room.
.EP

.SH Example
.SI 5
> playerkillers
There are 3 player killers logged in:
Harbinger          Pilla          Vixen
> playerkillers here
The player killers in the room currently are Pilla and Vixen.
> playerk
There are 4 player killers logged in:
Shiannar          Shaydz           Pilla         Vixen
.EI

.SH See also
.SP 5 5
qwho, users, who, playerkilling
.EP
